<% layout('layout') -%>


	
<helpbox>



 <br> <br>
 	<helpleft>
 	<b>
	How do I join? <br>
	</b>
	</helpleft>
	 <br>
	 <helpleft>
	You will spawn automatically as long as you are in the twitch channel and will stay logged on until you leave. <br>
	</helpleft>
	
	  <br> <br>
 	<helpleft>
 	<b>
	What do I get for leveling up? <br>
	</b>
	</helpleft>
	 <br>
	 <helpleft>
	You will receive 2 health for every level you have gained and 1 damage for every 3 levels you have gained. <br>
	</helpleft>
	 <br>
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	<b>
	How do I pick up items? <br>
	</b>
	</helpleft>
	
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	You will pick up any items when your character walks over them; as long as you do not have full inventory.<br>
	</helpleft>
	<br>
	 <br>
	<helpleft>
	<b>
	What do the stats do? <br>
	</b>
	</helpleft>
	
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	Damage lets you kill monsters faster <br>
	</helpleft>
	

	<br>
	<helpleft>
	Health lets you live longer <br>
	</helpleft>
	

	<br>
	<helpleft>
	1 Armor reduces enemy damage by 1 <br>
	</helpleft>
	<br>

	<helpleft>
	Lifesteal gives that percent of your damage back as health (Currently nerfed to 5x of the shown value)<br>
	</helpleft>
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	Critical chance, chance to do a critical attack doing your damage*crit damage
	</helpleft>

	<br>
	<helpleft>
	You can also heal on crits.
	</helpleft>

	<br>
	 <br>
	<helpleft>
	<b>
	How do I know what item is better?<br>
	</b>
	</helpleft>
	
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	There are tons of people who will help you decide which item to use in both our discord and in the twitch channel. <br>
	</helpleft>
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	If you are brave enough you can also use your own build and let me know on your results! <br>
	</helpleft>

	<br>
	 <br>
	<helpleft>
	<b>
	What is the bank? <br>
	</b>
	</helpleft>
	
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	You can store items there that you may need or want to test out later on.  <br>
	</helpleft>

	<br>
	 <br>
	<helpleft>
	<b>
	What do the different classes do? <br>
	</b>
	</helpleft>
	
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	Intelligence will increase your damage by 1 for each point of intelligence if you are a wizard.<br>
	</helpleft>
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	Strength will increase your damage by 1 for each point of strength if you are a warrior.<br>
	</helpleft>
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	Dexterity will increase your damage by 1 for each point of dexterity if you are an archer.<br>
	</helpleft>

	<br>
	 <br>
	<helpleft>
	<b>
	Do I lose anything for dying? <br>
	</b>
	</helpleft>
	
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	You will not receive any penalty for dying. While you are dead, you will still gain experience gained by other players. <br>
	</helpleft>

	<br>
	 <br>
	<helpleft>
	<b>
	What happens when everyone dies? <br>
	</b>
	</helpleft>
	
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	A PVP event will occur, then the world will begin from the Forest and continue on (see maps below) <br>
	</helpleft>

	 <br>
	 <br>
	<helpleft>
	<b>
	How do the different maps work? <br>
	</b>
	</helpleft>
	
	<br>
	<helpleft>
	There are currently 10 maps: Forest, Swamp, Bog, Desert, Graveyard, Burning Fields, Cursed Ruins, Crypt, Ocean, and The End <br>
	</helpleft>

	<br>
	<helpleft>
	When The End is beaten, the world will reset to the Forest and everything in the world will become much stronger. <br>
	</helpleft>
	<br>
	 <br>
	</helpbox>

